    prognosis: 'AF is not immediately life-threatening but doubles mortality and increases stroke risk 5-fold. With appropriate anticoagulation, stroke risk reduced by 65%. Catheter ablation (PVI) offers 70-80% freedom from AF at 1 year in paroxysmal AF. 10-year outcomes: ~30% of paroxysmal AF progresses to persistent/permanent. Mortality driven by comorbidities (HF, MI, stroke) rather than AF itself. Lone AF (age <60, no structural disease) has excellent prognosis.',
