      diagnosticAlgorithm: ['1. Confirm severe hypertension (SBP >=180 or DBP >=120) x 2 readings both arms', '2. Assess for acute target organ damage: history, physical (neuro exam, fundoscopy, CVS), CXR, ECG, Cr/eGFR, urinalysis', '3. If any TOD = hypertensive emergency -> ICU -> IV antihypertensives', '4. Start IV infusion: Labetalol or Nicardipine (first line). Esmolol + nitroprusside if aortic dissection.', '5. Target BP: MAP -25% @ 1-2h. SBP 160-180 @ 6h. SBP 140-160 @ 24h.', '6. Identify and treat specific TOD: ACS (GTN + BB), HF (vasodilators + diuretics), encephalopathy (controlled lowering), ICH (permissive HTN per guidelines), dissection (SBP <120 + HR <60)', '7. Screen for secondary HTN: renal artery stenosis, CKD, phaeochromocytoma, hyperaldosteronism, OSA, pregnancy', '8. Transition to oral therapy when stable. Provide discharge education + follow-up.'],
